By end of this course students will be able toUnderstand how major theories of psychology are shaped by and may not generalize across cultures.Examine cross-cultural differences in self-construal, motivation and communication from Japanese perspective.Critically analyze the published research in cultural psychologyConduct a group research project and present findings.Write an individual paper connecting group research to broader course concepts.
